str2: Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.
Compound of heros and eidos; heroic; Herod, the name of four Jewish kings.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

str2: To send up (to a higher tribunal), send back. From ana and pempo; to send up or back.
To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 1st Person Plural
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.

str2: See! Lo! Behold! Look! Second person singular imperative middle voice of eido; used as imperative lo!

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.

str2: To do, perform, accomplish; be in any condition, i.e. I fare; I exact, require.
Worthy, worthy of, deserving, comparable, suitable. Probably from ago; deserving, comparable or suitable.
Death, physical or spiritual. From thnesko; death.
